Apple has released its picks for the best apps, movies, and songs on the App Store. The apps of the year were Procreate Pocket for iPhone, Froggipedia for iPad, Pixelmator Pro Sweat for Mac, and Sweat for Apple TV. It also awarded Drake with the artist of the year award, while Juice WRLD was awarded breakout artist of the year. Cardi B’s I Like It, featuring Bad Bunny and J. Balvin, was rated song of the year. Apple also compiled a playlist of South Africa’s 100 favourite songs, which includes local artists such as Lady Zamar, AKA, and Kwesta – although the list is dominated by international artists. According to Apple, the best movies of 2018 on iTunes were: